title: Something Spider Man adaptions should do
body:
Animate the spider so you feel sorry for it.

Its probably really stressed and scared, it shouldn’t come off like its moving in the perfect position to bite. It understands what is happening even less than usual, just full of energy and nowhere feels safe to hide.

tags: i'm being silly but i had to get it off my chest
summary: I saw a post earlier and honestly I feel like I'm overreacting but it kinda ticked me off. It was about MCU Spiderman and said...
body:
I saw a post earlier and honestly I feel like I’m overreacting but it kinda ticked me off. It was about MCU Spiderman and said that it’s important that Peter has a father figure and like, no, it’s not.

There’s nothing wrong with having a father figure but that doesn’t mean you need one. Speaking as someone who has been raised by one parent most of their life, comments like that just seem to imply that a single guardian isn’t enough and that’s not true at all.

Also Peter’s guardian is Aunt May, she’s worked her ass off to support Peter and loves him greatly. And not to mention that Peter has had a father figure before in the form of Uncle Ben.

It’s dumb but I really can’t stand comments like that. Having a father or mother figure is great but it’s not super important or needed. One parental figure can be enough for a child.
